      "content": "Strengthening the border and enforcing immigration laws is crucial to maintaining national security, protecting American jobs, and preserving the rule of law. Increased border security measures, such as physical barriers and advanced surveillance systems, will deter human traffickers, cartel smugglers, and terrorists from crossing the border undetected. Stricter immigration enforcement will also help to prevent the exploitation of vulnerable workers, reduce the strain on public resources, and ensure that those who enter the country do so legally and contribute to the economy. Furthermore, a robust immigration system will provide a pathway for skilled workers to enter the country, addressing labor shortages in key industries and driving economic growth.",
